By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Chairman of the Independent National Electoral (INEC), Mahmood Yakubu has announced the postponement of collation of election results till 11am Monday (tomorrow) after announcing Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress (APC) as the winner of Ekiti presidential election. According to the result released, the APC won with 20, 050 votes to win in the state while the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) came second with 89,554 votes and the Labour Party came third with 11, 397. Shortly after announcing the result, the INEC boss informed that there is no other state whose election results have arrived the collation centre and therefore announced that the commission has made arrangements to convey the Returning Officers to Abuja. Details shortly…..